Testing #9684.

I use the following code:

```
var largeArray = [];
for (var i = 0; i < 10000; i++) {
    largeArray.push(i);
}
console.log('created large array');
```

and get the following at the end of the array:
<img width="267" alt="screen shot 2016-07-26 at 6 14 55 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4674940/17160821/e5802dc0-535c-11e6-9e62-2dafe0b79cf9.png">

The end of the last range is incorrect and the node can not be opened.

- VSCode Version: Code 1.3.1 (e6b4afa53e9c0f54edef1673de9001e9f0f547ae, 2016-07-12T13:31:10.994Z)
- OS Version: Darwin x64 15.5.0

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a new file.
2. Set syntax to SASS/SCSS
3. `.foo {
   height: 20px;
   .bar {
     height: 10px;
   }
   width: 20px;
   display: block;
   }`

You will noticed that the properties after the nested block `.bar` like `width: 20px;` and `display: block;` will be devoid of proper coloring.

![screen shot 2016-07-26 at 3 03 52 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/129781/17157126/42ad5f9c-5342-11e6-8836-4b14de32aa69.png)
